n class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 21, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104arf1665702757675.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/arf1665702757675.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/arf1665702757675.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"arf1665702757675\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">image\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"arf1665702757675__image_304713\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface data type containing binary data.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"arf1665702757675__topic_d92600e1_d92601e1_d92602e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arf1665702757675__p_d92603e1_d92604e1_d92605e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">image</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ParameterName</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Direction</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arf1665702757675__p_d92606e1_d92607e1_d92608e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">image</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">VariableName</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"arf1665702757675__topic_d61627e1_d61628e1_d61629e1_d61630e1_d61631e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d448327e84\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arf1665702757675__d5970e20\">Use in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">params</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">variables</span> blocks to define the data type of a parameter or variable. The data type can be selected when defining fields, global variables, and component variables.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"arf1665702757675__topic_d61632e1_d61633e1_d61634e1_d61635e1_d61636e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d448327e99\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arf1665702757675__p_d92618e1_d92619e1_d92620e1\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">image</span> data type for fields that contain images from the database, glyphs, disk files, or third-party filters.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arf1665702757675__p_d92621e1_d92622e1_d92623e1\">No arithmetic operations can be applied to this kind of data.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arf1665702757675__p_d92624e1_d92625e1_d92626e1\">It is not possible to directly compare two parameters,\n            variables, or fields that use the data type <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">raw</span> or\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">image</span>—they will always evaluate to <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code>. An\n            alternative is to calculate and compare a hash of the data.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qsj1704711355836.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Image Handling</a><p>Uniface can display and print pictures that are stored as image files on disk, as glyphs, or BLOBs in a database. The type of picture can affect performance.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vee1714313798310.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Data Handling in ProcScript</a><p>The ProcScript language enables you to convert data from one type to another, perform arithmetic operations, extract data values, and perform string substitution. Uniface carries out implicit type conversion whenever necessary, for example, when assignments are made between non-matching data types or when comparing non-matching data types. The ProcScript language also provides a number of functions that allow you to convert from one data type to another.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rxi1665702670406.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Packing Codes for Other Data</a><p>String, Image, and Raw data can be mapped to a variety of packing codes, including W for Unicode characters.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525843\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525843\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "image Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 21, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 image Uniface data type containing binary data. image ParameterName : Direction image VariableName Use Use in params and variables blocks to define the data type of a parameter or variable. The data type can be selected when defining fields, global variables, and component variables. Description Use the image data type for fields that contain images from the database, glyphs, disk files, or third-party filters. No arithmetic operations can be applied to this kind of data. It is not possible to directly compare two parameters, variables, or fields that use the data type raw or image —they will always evaluate to True . An alternative is to calculate and compare a hash of the data. Related Links Image Handling Uniface can display and print pictures that are stored as image files on disk, as glyphs, or BLOBs in a database. The type of picture can affect performance. Data Handling in ProcScript The ProcScript language enables you to convert data from one type to another, perform arithmetic operations, extract data values, and perform string substitution. Uniface carries out implicit type conversion whenever necessary, for example, when assignments are made between non-matching data types or when comparing non-matching data types. The ProcScript language also provides a number of functions that allow you to convert from one data type to another. Packing Codes for Other Data String, Image, and Raw data can be mapped to a variety of packing codes, including W for Unicode characters. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}